description: 0008KEPLER<--CENTROID:  The Kepler space telescope was launched by NASA in early 2009 to discover Earth-size planets orbiting other stars.  In May the telescope began beaming data back to Earth.  This piece examines a two hour slice (0000) of the commissioning data released by the Kepler project. Three variables (time/TIME, electrons/SAP_FLUX, centroid/MOM_CENTR1) and their relationship to each other, defines the raw input for this abstraction.  This abstracted set is viewed from the perspective of the "centroid" axis.

name: DATAbstract
description: 0011KEPLER<--CENTROID:  The Kepler space telescope was launched by NASA in early 2009 to discover Earth-size planets orbiting other stars.  In May the telescope began beaming data back to Earth.  This piece examines a two hour slice (0000) of the commissioning data released by the Kepler project. Three variables (time/TIME, electrons/SAP_FLUX, centroid/MOM_CENTR1) and their relationship to each other, defines the raw input for this abstraction.  This abstracted set is viewed from the perspective of the "centroid" axis.

description: Base data set used for creation of the DATAbstract GEN00 cryptoCANDLE set.  This data was pulled from Binance 30 min trading API consisting of 30 minute volume and price intervals.  Each subset captures 75 days of data oriented around the peak price over the first six months of 2021.  The full set consists of 32 individual subsets of 3,600 points.  Subsets are manipulated through the PROT V4 algorithm to generate a point cloud consisting of ~13 million points used for the image generation.

description: 0012KEPLER<--TIME:  The Kepler space telescope was launched by NASA in early 2009 to discover Earth-size planets orbiting other stars.  In May the telescope began beaming data back to Earth.  This piece examines a two hour slice (0000) of the commissioning data released by the Kepler project. Three variables (time/TIME, electrons/SAP_FLUX, centroid/MOM_CENTR1) and their relationship to each other, defines the raw input for this abstraction.  This abstracted set is viewed from the perspective of the "time" axis.
title: lightCURVE|30

description: 0000KEPLER<--CENTROID:  The Kepler space telescope was launched by NASA in early 2009 to discover Earth-size planets orbiting other stars.  In May the telescope began beaming data back to Earth.  This piece examines a two hour slice (0000) of the commissioning data released by the Kepler project. Three variables (time/TIME, electrons/SAP_FLUX, centroid/MOM_CENTR1) and their relationship to each other, defines the raw input for this abstraction.  This abstracted set is viewed from the perspective of the "centroid" axis.

name: DATAbstract
description: 0010KEPLER<--ELECTRONS:  The Kepler space telescope was launched by NASA in early 2009 to discover Earth-size planets orbiting other stars.  In May the telescope began beaming data back to Earth.  This piece examines a two hour slice (0000) of the commissioning data released by the Kepler project. Three variables (time/TIME, electrons/SAP_FLUX, centroid/MOM_CENTR1) and their relationship to each other, defines the raw input for this abstraction.  This abstracted set is viewed from the perspective of the "electron" axis.
title: lightCURVE|24

name: DATAbstract
description: LTC-USDT~climb to 408 (2-22-2021<->5-8-2021):  A 75 day view of the climb to the peak trading price of the LTC market in the first 6 months of 2021.   The price and volume data over 30 min intervals is plotted and mathmatically transformed providing a glimpse of the complex relationships found within the numbers.
title: cryptoCANDLE|10-LTC-climb

name: DATAbstract
description: 0012KEPLER<--CENTROID:  The Kepler space telescope was launched by NASA in early 2009 to discover Earth-size planets orbiting other stars.  In May the telescope began beaming data back to Earth.  This piece examines a two hour slice (0000) of the commissioning data released by the Kepler project. Three variables (time/TIME, electrons/SAP_FLUX, centroid/MOM_CENTR1) and their relationship to each other, defines the raw input for this abstraction.  This abstracted set is viewed from the perspective of the "centroid" axis.
title: lightCURVE|28
